programme.title: Villarreal x Atlético de Madrid
programme.desc: Pela 25ª rodada, o Villarreal recebe o Atlético de Madrid no Estádio de la Ceramica. O time da casa não vence há, pelo menos, cinco partidas e tenta se recuperar. Os Colchoneros buscam abrir mais vantagem na liderança.

programme.title: The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn Part 2
programme.desc: The Volturi are in uproar upon learning of the birth of Edward and Bella's child, Renesmee. In order to protect the innocent child from destruction, the Cullens and the wolves come together in battle.

programme.title: A Call to Spy
programme.desc: A desperate Winston Churchill orders his new spy agency to recruit and train women as spies in the early days of WWII, leading a trio of female agents to go undercover in France. Risking their lives to build a resistance movement and sabotage the Nazis.

programme.title: No Country for Old Men
programme.desc: A welder finds $2 million at the site of a drug exchange near the border. Deciding to keep the money, he soon finds himself being chased by a psychotic killer who also wants the money. The hit man terrorizes his prey while being chased by a sheriff.

programme.title: Born on the Fourth of July
programme.desc: A small-town athlete enthusiastically enlists to fight in the Vietnam War and returns home, paralyzed from the chest down. After a nightmarish stint in a veterans' hospital, he pulls his life together and becomes an anti-war activist in the process.

programme.title: In the Line of Fire
programme.desc: A U.S. Secret Service agent, who was unable to prevent Kennedy's murder, vows to stop a madman who plans to assassinate the president.

programme.title: The Untouchables
programme.desc: Federal agent Eliot Ness forms a fearless foursome to take on crime boss Al Capone.

programme.title: No Way Out
programme.desc: The secretary of defence and his loyal aid try to cover up the murder of a call girl.

programme.title: The Crying Game
programme.desc: After a kidnapped British soldier left in his charge is accidentally killed, IRA soldier Fergus flees to England, where he keeps his promise to look after the soldier's distraught girlfriend, with whom Fergus soon finds himself falling in love.

programme.title: The Captive
programme.desc: Eight years after the disappearance of a girl, incidents indicate she could be alive. Her parents and the police try to solve the mystery of her disappearance.

programme.title: Locke
programme.desc: A happy and successful construction manager leaves an important job in Birmingham one day and sets out for London. During the drive, he receives a phone call that sets off a series of events that threatens to unravel his entire life.

programme.title: Spy Game
programme.desc: A CIA agent works against time and the agency to help free his former protégé.

programme.title: Resistance
programme.desc: Based on the true story of Marcel Marceau who joined the French Resistance and saved children from the Nazis.
Two soldiers’ race across enemy territory to deliver a message that could save lives of 1,600 soldiers.

programme.title: L Word Mississippi: Hate the Sin
programme.desc: Meet a group of gay women who are living in the South. They must face difficulties in their lives, including bigotry, bullying, sexism and racism.

programme.title: Brokeback Mountain
programme.desc: Two cowboys develop an intimate relationship in 1960s Wyoming, spanning over 20 years, despite both of them being married to women.

programme.title: Queer as Folk
programme.desc: Michael and Justin join forces to create their own comic book.

programme.title: Queer as Folk
programme.desc: Brian ignores Justin's birthday, so Melanie and Lindsay take him to a violin concert.

programme.title: Queer as Folk
programme.desc: Brian has to cancel plans with Justin to impress his new boss.

programme.title: Queer as Folk
programme.desc: Michael's fears come true when Ben is hospitalized; Justin wishes Brian was more romantic.

programme.title: Summerland
programme.desc: A reclusive writer from Southern England, is entrusted with the care of a young evacuee from London. As WW II rages across the channel, the evacuee rekindles suppressed feelings and emotions from the writer's past and the two bond.

programme.title: The L Word
programme.desc: Bette and Tina deal with parenting Angelica. Dana's and Alice's relationship changes. Jenny copes with the idea of staying at her parents' home.

programme.title: The L Word
programme.desc: As flamboyant party promoter Billie Blaikie sets up shop at The Planet, Bette feels her life is out of her control. Meanwhile, Alice refuses to let Helena throw out her life-size cut-out of Dana and Jenny wants to be more than just friends with Moira.

programme.title: The L Word
programme.desc: Tina goes to work for Helena when Bette refuses to curb her spending. Meanwhile, Jenny brings Moira home to L.A. and introduces her to the girls and Alice continues her emotional tailspin over losing Dana.

programme.title: Black Monday
programme.desc: Mo tries to keep up with Nomi but he comes to realize that time catches up with us all when he finds he can't party like he used to. Meanwhile, Dawn's attempt to get him to slow down backfires.

programme.title: Flatbush Misdemeanors
programme.desc: Kevin, bummed from being stood up by Jasmine and ripped off by a local Brooklyn rapper, spends a shrooms-filled night out with his successful sister which leads to a series of revelations.

programme.title: The Lookout
programme.desc: A promising hockey player becomes an amnesiac after a tragic car accident. While working in the bank, a gang member befriends him and manipulates him into joining their heist.

programme.title: Out of Time
programme.desc: A Florida police chief must solve a double murder before he himself falls under suspicion.

programme.title: The Turning
programme.desc: An adaptation of Henry James' novella 'The Turn of the Screw,' the story revolves around a governess hired to tutor an heiress who witnessed her parents' death. After strange events take place, the governess begins to suspect there's more to the story.
